Verbatim Block Visual Test

This document demonstrates all verbatim block types in Scripta,
showing each with and without options where applicable.

**Math Blocks:**
- `math` - Display math
- `equation` - Numbered equation (with optional `label`)
- `aligned` - Aligned multi-line equations
- `array` - Math arrays/matrices (with column format argument)
- `chem` - Chemical equations

**Code and Text:**
- `code` - Syntax-highlighted code (with optional language)
- `verse` - Poetry with italic styling
- `verbatim` - Raw preformatted text

**Tables:**
- `table` / `textarray` - Tables with `&` separator
- `csvtable` - CSV tables (with optional `title`)
- `datatable` - Raw data display

**Media:**
- `image` - Images with options:
  - Arguments: `expandable`
  - Properties: `width`, `float`, `ypadding`, `description`, `figure`, `caption`
- `iframe` - Embedded content (with `width`, `height`)

**Graphics (require JS integration):**
- `svg` - Inline SVG
- `tikz` - TikZ diagrams
- `quiver` - Commutative diagrams
- `chart` - Charts

**Configuration (hidden):**
- `mathmacros` - Define LaTeX macros
- `textmacros` - Define text macros
- `settings`, `load`, `load-data`, `hide`, `docinfo`, `load-files`, `include`, `setup`



# Math Blocks

## Basic Math (display mode)

The `math` block renders LaTeX mathematics in display mode:

| math
\int_0^\infty e^{-x^2} dx = \frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}


## Numbered Equation

The `equation` block creates a numbered equation:

| equation
E = mc^2

With a label for cross-referencing:

| equation label:einstein
E = mc^2


## Aligned Equations

The `aligned` block renders multi-line aligned equations:

| aligned
f(x) &= x^2 + 2x + 1 \\
     &= (x + 1)^2


## Math Array

The `array` block creates a matrix or array with column alignment.
The argument specifies column format (c=center, l=left, r=right):

| array ccc
1 & 2 & 3 \\
4 & 5 & 6 \\
7 & 8 & 9


# Chemistry

## Chemical Equations

The `chem` block uses mhchem notation for chemical equations:

| chem
2H2 + O2 -> 2H2O

Another example:

| chem
CH3COOH + NaOH -> CH3COONa + H2O


# Code Blocks

## Basic Code Block

The `code` block displays syntax-highlighted code:

| code
function factorial(n) {
    if (n <= 1) return 1;
    return n * factorial(n - 1);
}

## Code with Language Specification

| code elm
renderText : String -> Html Msg
renderText str =
    Html.span [] [ Html.text str ]


# Poetry and Verse

## Verse Block

The `verse` block displays poetry with preserved line breaks and italic styling:

| verse
Roses are red,
Violets are blue,
Scripta is wonderful,
And so are you!


# Tables

## Text Table (textarray)

The `table` or `textarray` block uses `&` as column separator:

| table
Name & Age & City
Alice & 30 & New York
Bob & 25 & Los Angeles
Carol & 35 & Chicago


## CSV Table

The `csvtable` block parses comma-separated values:

| csvtable
Product,Q1,Q2,Q3,Q4
Widgets,100,150,200,250
Gadgets,50,75,100,125
Sprockets,30,45,60,75

With a title property:

| csvtable title:Quarterly Sales Report
Product,Q1,Q2,Q3,Q4
Widgets,100,150,200,250
Gadgets,50,75,100,125


# Data Display

## Data Table

The `datatable` block displays raw data in preformatted style:

| datatable
x    y    z
1    2    3
4    5    6
7    8    9


# Raw Verbatim Text

## Verbatim Block

The `verbatim` block preserves exact spacing and formatting:

| verbatim
This   text   has   preserved   spacing.
    Indentation is maintained.
        All formatting is kept as-is.


# Images

## Basic Image

The `image` block displays an image from a URL:

| image
https://picsum.photos/200/150

## Image with Width

| image width:300
https://picsum.photos/400/300

## Image with Caption and Figure Number

| image figure:1 caption:A sample image from Lorem Picsum
https://picsum.photos/300/200

## Expandable Image

Click the thumbnail to view full size (click overlay to close):

| image expandable width:200 caption:Click to expand
https://picsum.photos/600/400

## Floated Image

| image float:left width:150
https://picsum.photos/150/100

This text wraps around the floated image on the left.
The image has a small top margin to align with the text baseline.
When using float, the image becomes part of the text flow
and subsequent content will wrap around it naturally.
This is useful for magazine-style layouts where images
are integrated with the surrounding text content.

## Image with Fill Width

| image width:fill
https://picsum.photos/800/200


# Embedded Content

## Iframe

The `iframe` block embeds external content:

| iframe
https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ

With custom dimensions:

| iframe width:400 height:300
https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ


# Graphics Placeholders

These blocks require external JavaScript integration:

## SVG

| svg
<svg width="100" height="100">
  <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="40" fill="red" />
</svg>

## TikZ Diagram

| tikz
\begin{tikzpicture}
\draw (0,0) -- (1,1);
\end{tikzpicture}

## Quiver Diagram

| quiver
[quiver diagram data goes here]

## Chart

| chart
type: bar
data: 10, 20, 30, 40


# Macro Definitions

## Math Macros (Hidden)

Define macros for use in math blocks:

| mathmacros
\newcommand{\R}{\mathbb{R}}
\newcommand{\norm}[1]{\left\| #1 \right\|}

Now we can use the macros:

| math
\norm{x} \in \R

## Text Macros (Hidden)

| textmacros
\newcommand{\version}{3.0}


# Hidden/Configuration Blocks

These blocks are processed but produce no visible output:

## Settings Block

| settings
theme: dark
fontSize: 14

## Load Block

| load
/path/to/external/file.md


